What is System design?

 -> System design is the process of designing the architecture, components and interfaces for a system so that it meets end user requirements. It is important for anyone who wants to build robust,
scalable and efficient software application.
 -> Whether you are building smal-scale application or larger one, understanding system requirements help you to architect the solution that can handle real world complexities.

Steps for getting started with System design:

1. Understand the requirements
2. Design the system architecture.
3. Choose the technology.
4. design the modules.
5. Plan for scalability
6. Test and validate.

Understanding the requirements

->  Gather and analyze the business need of the requirements. Work with stakeholders and documents the requirements clearly.
This helps avoid mistakes later in development. Fo eg : user login, online payment, order placement.

Design the system architecture:

-> overall structure of the system is defined. It involves apis, services,and database. high level view of the system. For eg:
Order service, payment service, checkout service.

Choose technology

-> This includes programming languages, databases, frameworks and tools that fits for the requirements. For eg : React for frontend,
Node js for backend, MongoDB for database.

Design Modules

-> The system is divided into modules or componenets each with a specific responsibility.

